The White House Office of the Press Secretary held a press call to preview the upcoming United Nations General Assembly (UNGA) events. The call was attended by three senior administration officials: Ben Rhodes, Deputy National Security Advisor for Strategic Communications; Steve Pomper, NSC Senior Director for Multilateral Affairs; and Celeste Wallander, NSC Senior Director for Russia. The main topics discussed during the call were the President's schedule at the UNGA, including his speech at the General Assembly, his meetings with various world leaders, and the focus on global challenges such as development, peacekeeping, climate change, and countering ISIL. The officials also mentioned the bilateral meeting with President Putin of Russia, where they planned to discuss the situation in Ukraine and Russia's involvement in Syria. They emphasized the importance of diplomacy and international cooperation in addressing global issues.